#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Collaboration between the Cape Peninsula University of Technology and its student representative council is yielding results. The institution says it has been able to accommodate most of its students. And that adopting an inclusive approach has helped a great deal. WATCH | CPUT SRC threatens strike action However, the university says all its student housing is now full. "We have had an experience whereby there has been a larger than usual influx of students during the registration process," says CPUT's Gilingwe Mayende. "This resulted in us having to deal with an additional number of students who needs to be assisted with accommodation," he says.